reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: I got this for next to my bed, and it works perfectly. I was skeptical at first, because of how cheap it was, and don't get me wrong. It is not a super super strong piece, but it is definitely perfect for what I need it for. It's almost like a laminate Woodish material. Again for the price and all things considered it's definitely very sturdy. Complaint was that it did come in a lot of pieces, and took me about an hour and a half to two hours to put together. Instructions were great and made it very simple. Just time-consuming. We recommend this to someone who's looking for something but doesn't want to spend a ton of money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to go beside the bed in my small, newly re-done guest bedroom. It is just perfect. I love the light color options, the charging port, the style, the storage. It was easy to assemble, looks amazing, is just the right size, and is sturdy. Highly recommend! 10 out of 10!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was concerned at first because some pieced looked cheap and fragile. Once I got it assembled it seems perfectly sturdy though. I like the outlets and RGB nightlight. I bought it because it is taller than the other nightstands of this type and price range. I am happy with it. It took a while to put together but didn't have any problems. I am satisfied with purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to follow instructions
reviews.reviewText: This was the easiest piece of furniture I've ever had to put together on my own. The instructions were so easy to follow and ALL the pieces were quality pieces. Looks great with the LED lights on and love the changing colors, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great features for a night stand
reviews.reviewText: I purchased 2 identical nightstands because of it’s great features, now I am in my early 70’s and it took me less than an hour to assemble each one. The drilling and fit are precise and the hardware was perfectly marked, so no guesswork as to what should be used next and even the proper screwdriver was supplied. The instructions are easy to follow. The finished nightstand looks very nice, the ledge around the top prevents things from falling off, the outlet and USB ports are a nice feature. I personally won’t use the LED lighting but it would be nice for someone else.One of the boxes had 2 missing parts, I contacted customer service by email, they responded without delay and promptly shipped an entire additional nightstand. Great product, excellent customer service and great value for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Nice LITTLE nighstand
reviews.reviewText: The material is normal and easy to put together but the size is VERY SMALL for $90. You can find something bigger and better in IKEA for less. Is very sturdy and the storage space is small. Not worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My husband and I built these together. Took us an hour each nightstand. Instructions were easy and helpful! They are very nice nightstands for a good price and probably the best you can get besides real wood. We added height risers underneath bc our bed is so high.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Smaller than images appear, but I like it
reviews.reviewText: As soon as I opened the instructions packet I was so happy so see how perfectly all parts were labeled, and the pictures explained each step clearly. This is very important! But they weren't kidding when they said that it a 2 person job. You need someone to hold the parts together while you attach them. I had my tween help me so it took about 2 hours instead of the suggested 40 minutes. The LED light strips and built in charge ports are very cool. My only complaints are that the images shown in the ad suggest that it looks bigger than it actually is. It is very small for a night stand but could maybe work better as an end table? I should have looked at the measurements instead. Also, it is hard to believe that it will support 50lbs., but I don't intend to try it. The bottom of the drawers is thin like cardboard, but the sides are well supported and slide in and out well without falling out. It is a good buy, but maybe not worth the price.
